    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-02-03T12:35:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-02-03T12:35:00-05:00" n="599"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d599">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.9131/108: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Engert</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tehran</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-02-03T21:00:00+03:25"
                            >February 3, 1940—9 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received February 5—4:45 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>26. Personal for Murray.<note n="62" xml:id="d599fn62">Wallace Murray, Chief of
                        the Division of Near Eastern Affairs.</note> My 25 of today. Whatever the
                    ultimate reaction of our competent authorities might be to the scheme outlined
                    may I suggest that a courteous reply be sent at once indicating that it would be
                    given serious consideration? Such a reply, coming at a psychological moment when
                    we are trying to break a deadlock in connection with the evaluation of school
                        properties,<note n="63" xml:id="d599fn63">Missionary school properties
                        expropriated by the Iranian Government. For correspondence, see <ref
                            target="#pg_693">pp. 693</ref> ff.</note> might help.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Engert</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
